{# HyperWeave Banner Frame — Paradigm-dispatched (Principle 26).

   Banner is a pure dispatcher: defs + content are included per-paradigm.
   Built-in paradigms:
     "default" → editorial grid + triple-layer hero text (brutalist look)
     "chrome"  → motorsport italic Impact, env-map fill, accent stripe labels

   Banner also has a `variant` axis (compact/full) that controls font-size.
   Paradigm is the structural axis; variant is the dimensional axis.
   Extends document.svg.j2. #}
{% extends "document.svg.j2" %}

{% block defs %}
{% include "frames/banner/" ~ (paradigm | default("default")) ~ "-defs.j2" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{% set bw = width | default(1200) %}
{% set bh = height | default(600) %}
{% set text_cx = bw // 2 %}
{% set is_full = (banner_variant | default('full')) == 'full' %}
{% include "frames/banner/" ~ (paradigm | default("default")) ~ "-content.j2" %}
{% endblock %}
